Given a list of integers, write a Java 8 program to separate the odd and even numbers into two separate lists.

import java.util.Arrays;
import java.util.List;
import java.util.stream.Collectors;

public class EvenOrOdd {
    public static void main(String[] args){
        List<Integer> list = Arrays.asList(1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9);
        List<Integer> evenNumbers = list.stream().filter(x->x%2==0).collect(Collectors.toList());
        List<Integer> oddNumbers = list.stream().filter(x->x%2!=0).collect(Collectors.toList());
        System.out.println("evenNumbers : " + evenNumbers);
        System.out.println("oddNumbers : " + oddNumbers);
    }
}


O/P:

evenNumbers : [2, 4, 6, 8]
oddNumbers : [1, 3, 5, 7, 9]
